The paper deals with crowd counting, which is a computer vision problem, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper proposes an end-to-end framework that uses attention-guided detection and density estimation, which involves machine learning techniques such as regression and decision-making. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models and convolutional neural networks, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
